    {
      "id": "93",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Andrius",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/126656441db6468e7c76d32be6953935_2413593655697833579.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Thousands of years ago, an ancient god gave powers to Andrius, so he became King of the North Wind. He was a noble soul who protected Wolvendom. When the wolfpack was imperiled, he emerged in the form of a wolf and showed forth its fangs and claws.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/fc0e41ddd06dc6fc637d16969e0876e7_3964897041697431359.jpg"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "About 3,000 years ago, the Great Wolf King of the North waged a war with the God of Storm, Decarabian. Andrius froze Mondstadt and forced Decarabian to create walls of storms around Old Mondstadt (now Stormterror's Lair). When the God of Storm was overthrown and Barbatos became the new Archon, Andrius stopped fighting. He finally realized the chilling north wind could only extinguish life, not nurture it; therefore, Boreas let his powers freely flow into the land to protect it and its inhabitants. Andrius allowed his physical body to die and took on the form of a wolf made of ice and wind.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/b34ebc96617bb4a954870f59cfee6165_2844330280309193709.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "When, 1,000 years ago, the Aristocracy ruling Mondstadt was overthrown by the slave Vennessa, who then founded the Knights of Favonius and convened the Four Winds, Andrius became one of the Four Winds protecting Mondstadt. Once upon a time, the Temple of the Wolf was built for him, where people worshiped the Wolf of the North, but over time, the Four Winds were forgotten.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Many years ago, a mechanism called the \"Field Tiller\" accidentally ended up in Andrius's arena, and he mistook the mechanism for a brave man who challenged him. The machine could not think, but every part of it was designed for killing and fighting. It could spin, fly high into the air, and shoot fireballs. In the end, Andrius was able to defeat the machine, but it managed to leave the arena before falling. For the people of ancient Mondstadt, the \"Field Tiller\" became the \"Tyrant's Final Fury,\" as they could not understand the true nature of the mechanism. This machine was the prototype for all the Ruin Guards made in Khaenri'ah and possessed the Eye of the first Field Tiller, with the help of which the Abyss Order, opposed to the Seven Kingdoms, tried to create a mechanical deity to overthrow the gods of Celestia from their thrones.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Nowadays, the wolves of Wolvendom have almost no contact with people, but one day they accepted a child into their pack, later named Razor, whom they consider their \"Lupical,\" that is, family. One day, the Abyss Order wanted Andrius to serve them, and in return, they promised the spirit to return his divine powers. The Abyss Herald attempted to perform a ritual to possess the mind of the King of the North, just as the Abyss mage once poisoned the mind of the Dragon of the East, Dvalin. The Herald lured Andrius under the pretense of challenging him to battle but was stopped by Razor and the Traveler.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
